1
00:02:03,010 --> 00:02:04,520
Are you okay?

2
00:02:03,950 --> 00:02:04,520
Y-Yeah.

3
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:10,980
Koza! Are you all right?!

4
00:02:10,980 --> 00:02:11,690
Y-Yeah.

5
00:02:11,940 --> 00:02:15,410
You've still got that bullet wound
from Nanohana...

6
00:02:16,950 --> 00:02:21,240
This is a battlefield.
Something like that is trivial here.

7
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,210
Never mind me.

8
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,670
Somehow, I need to get a horse.

9
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:28,160
We need to make it down this street
and straight through town

10
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:30,710
to reach the palace in the north block.

11
00:02:32,540 --> 00:02:35,390
The palace? What are
you planning to do?

12
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:39,100
Demand King Cobra's surrender.

13
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:41,090
Don't be foolish!

14
00:02:41,090 --> 00:02:45,850
The north block is where Chaka, Pell,
and the Royal Army's main forces are!

15
00:02:45,850 --> 00:02:50,710
It's too dangerous! We haven't even
been able to all regroup yet!

16
00:02:50,710 --> 00:02:54,490
Shouldn't we wait on reinforcements
from the rest of the country?

17
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:58,000
It's already too late as it is.

18
00:02:58,650 --> 00:02:59,780
Give me a hand!

19
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:02,540
Hey, Koza!

20
00:03:14,210 --> 00:03:17,230
Halt! Are you with the Rebel Army?!

21
00:03:18,870 --> 00:03:22,520
There's nothing ahead
in the north block but the palace!

22
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:24,640
Do you understand?!

23
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:29,280
If you're not a combatant,
then leave the vicinity immediately!

24
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:33,710
Hey, lady! Are you listening?!
This is no playground!

25
00:03:34,540 --> 00:03:36,450
I know!

26
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:39,510
Princess Vivi!

27
00:03:39,510 --> 00:03:41,290
It couldn't be!

28
00:03:41,290 --> 00:03:43,070
Is it really her?

29
00:03:44,630 --> 00:03:47,450
Where is my father?
Where is he currently?

30
00:03:47,450 --> 00:03:48,990
W-Well, the thing is...

31
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,420
In that case...

32
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:53,960
take me to Chaka!

33
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:57,190
There's something I want him to do!

34
00:04:22,290 --> 00:04:24,580
You bastard...!

35
00:04:25,910 --> 00:04:27,490
What a kick...

36
00:04:27,490 --> 00:04:30,460
Imagine that—he's able to compete
with my okama kenpo!

37
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:33,800
Out of my way!

38
00:04:34,300 --> 00:04:38,050
I told you, if you want to get by,
you'll have to defeat me first.

39
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:42,110
You can keep pushing your luck then.

40
00:04:42,110 --> 00:04:45,380
Day after day, lesson after lesson...

41
00:04:45,380 --> 00:04:51,900
I've honed my okama kenpo—
it won't be beaten by the likes of you!

42
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:57,810
Don't bother trying
to escape my fists!

43
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:01,340
Okama Kenpo!

44
00:05:15,790 --> 00:05:19,330
Drunken Swan Soiree!

45
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:29,310
This is going nowhere.
I'm settling this here and now!

46
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,860
Collier Shoot!

47
00:05:33,930 --> 00:05:34,860
Un!

48
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:36,480
Épaule!

49
00:05:35,880 --> 00:05:36,480
Deux!

50
00:05:38,010 --> 00:05:39,110
Côtelette!

51
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:39,110
Ourrois!

52
00:05:41,210 --> 00:05:41,900
Selle!

53
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:43,410
Un!

54
00:05:44,030 --> 00:05:45,750
Poitrine!

55
00:05:44,490 --> 00:05:45,750
Deux!

56
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:46,660
Gigot!

57
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:46,660
Korrois!

58
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:49,410
Okama Kenpo!

59
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:53,540
Mouton Shot!

60
00:05:53,540 --> 00:05:55,210
Swan Arabesque!

61
00:06:14,490 --> 00:06:18,190
That bastard blocked...
my Mouton Shot?

62
00:06:20,170 --> 00:06:24,090
That insignificant cook stopped...
my Swan Arabesque?

63
00:06:25,310 --> 00:06:27,120
You've got to be clowning me!

64
00:06:29,030 --> 00:06:33,040
Okay, fine! I mean business!
From now on, I mean business!

65
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:35,000
Try me.

66
00:06:35,240 --> 00:06:39,960
You haven't figured out
my ability yet, have you?

67
00:06:40,530 --> 00:06:43,170
What's remarkable is
the extent of my memory.

68
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:48,340
Using it allows me to devise,
you could say, a type of montage!

69
00:06:49,350 --> 00:06:52,530
When you see this,
you will laugh until you collapse.

70
00:06:53,930 --> 00:06:54,890
First...

71
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:57,860
the world's strangest hair.

72
00:06:58,370 --> 00:07:00,820
Then, the world's strangest eyes...

73
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:03,770
The world's strangest nose...

74
00:07:03,770 --> 00:07:06,780
The world's strangest mouth...

75
00:07:07,370 --> 00:07:09,240
Now, take a good, long look!

76
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:13,000
It's time for the big unveiling!

77
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:16,210
Clone-Clone Montage!

78
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:28,660
That was just 90 percent
of your own face, wasn't it?

79
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:31,800
An opening!

80
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,930
Stop playing games, you birdbrain!

81
00:07:34,930 --> 00:07:39,330
Don't you have a heart, you devil?!

82
00:07:39,770 --> 00:07:43,110
I don't have time
to entertain your gimmick.

83
00:07:43,350 --> 00:07:46,980
Gimmick? No! This is no gimmick!

84
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:49,110
Once upon a time,
there was someone—

85
00:07:49,110 --> 00:07:53,080
a man made powerless against me
through only his feelings of friendship.

86
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:57,260
Love is everything.
People must have love.

87
00:07:57,260 --> 00:08:01,040
Your love needs me.

88
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:57,260
So that's it. I have an idea, now...

89
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:01,040
about what you're plotting.

90
00:08:01,610 --> 00:08:02,960
Go on, try to lay a hand on–

91
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:09,710
H-How could you?!
That was the face of your friend!

92
00:08:09,710 --> 00:08:13,010
Is that how you treat your friends?!

93
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,550
What are you, stupid?

94
00:08:15,550 --> 00:08:18,850
No matter who you change into, you are still you.

95
00:08:19,830 --> 00:08:23,360
I'm not the sort to be
deceived by such imitations.

96
00:08:25,110 --> 00:08:28,030
A person's essence...
is their heart and soul!

97
00:08:32,670 --> 00:08:34,290
A person's heart and soul?

98
00:08:34,980 --> 00:08:36,010
You're so...

99
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:39,130
refined!

100
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:44,050
I'm embarrassed to have
been consumed by looks!

101
00:08:48,870 --> 00:08:51,050
Mellorine! Mellorine!

102
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:53,050
Mellorine! Mellorine!

103
00:08:44,740 --> 00:08:45,790
All right.

104
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:47,480
Even if I were to, say,
change into her,

105
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,300
Even if I were to, say,
change into her,

106
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:51,590
or any of your other friends,

107
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:53,050
it wouldn't mean anything.

108
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:59,060
Mellorine! Mellorine!

109
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:00,940
He's so easy to read.

110
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:07,230
What a fool.

111
00:09:08,890 --> 00:09:10,220
It's Princess Vivi!

112
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:12,950
It's true! The princess has returned!

113
00:09:12,950 --> 00:09:14,240
Why now of all times?

114
00:09:20,890 --> 00:09:25,090
Are you insane, Princess Vivi?!
If we did that...

115
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:33,710
If we did that, then what?
This land would fall into ruin?

116
00:09:33,710 --> 00:09:37,430
It wouldn't, would it?
This isn't Alabasta, after all.

117
00:09:41,470 --> 00:09:43,100
The Kingdom of Alabasta...

118
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:01,690
is the people, and right now
they're hurting each other.

119
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:05,840
They're the reason this place
became a country to begin with!

120
00:10:06,650 --> 00:10:10,300
If we can stop this war,
then that's reason enough!

121
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:16,190
Please! We just need to draw
everyone's attention for a moment...

122
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:20,180
I will come up with
something from there.

123
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,510
I swear, I will!

124
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:31,810
You must... destroy...

125
00:10:31,810 --> 00:10:32,950
this palace!

126
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:38,900
Wh-What...

127
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:42,810
What are you saying, Princess?!

128
00:10:42,810 --> 00:10:46,390
This palace has a 4,000-year history!

129
00:10:46,390 --> 00:10:48,710
Please end this absurd idea,
Princess Vivi!

130
00:10:48,710 --> 00:10:51,340
Commander Chaka, this is unwise!

131
00:10:52,190 --> 00:10:53,670
The king is not present!

132
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,680
We cannot allow you
to take action on your own!

133
00:11:00,970 --> 00:11:04,310
But, Your Majesty, at this rate,

134
00:11:04,310 --> 00:11:06,320
the country will be in mortal danger!

135
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:08,140
And what of it?

136
00:11:08,980 --> 00:11:15,570
You want to destroy our countrymen
without knowing who's pulling the strings?

137
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:19,620
That would be
the destruction of this country.

138
00:11:19,870 --> 00:11:21,870
We act immediately!

139
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:24,580
We're heading to
Crocodile's home, Rainbase!

140
00:11:25,510 --> 00:11:28,920
Forgive my words, but if we
turn against Crocodile now...

141
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:31,880
we'd be adding fuel
to the flames of unrest.

142
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:37,800
If we attack Rainbase, the Rebel Army will
use that as a chance to storm the palace!

143
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:43,420
And so what if the Rebel Army
were to take the palace?

144
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:47,810
Even if we, the Royal Army,
were to fall,

145
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:52,680
if we cut out the root of this,
the country will surely rise again.

146
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:55,650
It is not this palace
that we should be protecting,

147
00:11:55,650 --> 00:11:57,450
it is the people of this nation!

148
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,650
Remember...

149
00:12:01,950 --> 00:12:05,410
A country... is its people.

150
00:12:09,490 --> 00:12:10,750
Princess Vivi...

151
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:18,180
I shall do as you command!

152
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:22,300
You're the perfect example
of a guy that's all talk!

153
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:25,270
You don't even have
the strength to get up, do you?

154
00:12:27,420 --> 00:12:30,650
Don't think I'm just going to lie down
and be beaten like this!

155
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:33,230
No matter how much
you might look like Nami,

156
00:12:33,230 --> 00:12:35,310
you're still that idiot on the inside.

157
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:38,900
You damn birdbrain!
Don't get too cocky!

158
00:12:45,450 --> 00:12:47,790
Damn it! She's so cute!

159
00:12:48,410 --> 00:12:52,510
Aah, I must say,
this land is too hot for me.

160
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:55,300
I just want to take off
all my clothes.

161
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,880
I'll help!

162
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:58,630
Okama Chop!

163
00:13:00,090 --> 00:13:01,340
My eye!

164
00:13:01,340 --> 00:13:03,430
You birdbrain!

165
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,020
Kick Pointe!

166
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:16,360
There's no bite to your bark, huh?!

167
00:13:18,730 --> 00:13:20,240
You bastard...!

168
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:23,740
How dare you mess with me?!

169
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:27,370
Mascara Boomerang!

170
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:30,710
See you in hell!

171
00:13:31,290 --> 00:13:33,000
Oh, don't kick me.

172
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:44,670
Can't forget to catch them!

173
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:50,890
Playing with you is fun, but I can't
dawdle around too long, you know?

174
00:13:50,890 --> 00:13:54,060
Our job is to kill the princess, after all.

175
00:13:56,620 --> 00:13:59,520
I'm going to hurry up
and finish this now.

176
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:04,470
Ha! Twirl, twirl, I'm twirling around!

177
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:10,750
What?! Blow up the royal palace?!

178
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:14,830
Yeah. Orders have come down
to destroy the royal palace.

179
00:14:15,140 --> 00:14:17,840
We're going to destroy
the royal palace!

180
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,830
They can't be serious.

181
00:14:19,830 --> 00:14:22,470
That building holds
a 4,000-year history.

182
00:14:28,140 --> 00:14:29,470
How can I begin to explain...

183
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:32,390
this situation?

184
00:14:32,890 --> 00:14:35,160
It's okay, I understand.

185
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:39,400
There was nothing you could do
except to intercept the Rebel Army.

186
00:14:40,020 --> 00:14:44,160
In Igaram's absence, you've done well
to suppress the uprising for over two years.

187
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:47,590
But my journey was worth the risk.

188
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:52,370
I met some true friends,
who are going to save Alabasta.

189
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:57,030
Once the Royal Army
and the Rebel Army meet,

190
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:58,590
this country will be gone.

191
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,520
If you are the one and only hope
for preventing that,

192
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:05,020
then you have to survive, at all costs.

193
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:11,520
It doesn't matter what might happen
to any of us from this point on!

194
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:17,150
All of you, willing
to give even your lives,

195
00:15:17,990 --> 00:15:19,620
how are you faring now?

196
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:20,810
Princess Vivi...

197
00:15:20,810 --> 00:15:22,770
In the two years since I last saw you,

198
00:15:22,770 --> 00:15:25,660
you have become quite beautiful.

199
00:15:27,470 --> 00:15:30,190
Once we have seen this war through,

200
00:15:30,190 --> 00:15:33,620
I think a grand banquet
for those pirates is in order.

201
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:35,540
Chaka...

202
00:15:38,090 --> 00:15:39,920
Then gimme food.

203
00:15:40,870 --> 00:15:46,800
After I kick Crocodile's ass,
gimme food till I burst!

204
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:52,050
That's right, I believe in you.
Luffy, you'll be fine.

205
00:15:52,050 --> 00:15:55,270
I'm sure that you must have
defeated Crocodile.

206
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:57,760
Commander Chaka!

207
00:15:57,760 --> 00:15:58,730
What is it?

208
00:15:59,370 --> 00:16:02,350
Is it true that you plan
to bring down the royal palace?!

209
00:16:02,350 --> 00:16:04,560
The soldiers are setting explosives!

210
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:06,070
There must be some mistake!

211
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:09,030
I am the one who gave the order.

212
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:10,860
Princess Vivi!

213
00:16:10,860 --> 00:16:13,860
Please use as many
explosives as we have.

214
00:16:13,860 --> 00:16:16,120
In order to stop
the senseless fighting,

215
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:18,830
and to save the lives
of the people of Alabasta,

216
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:22,590
we will level the royal palace!

217
00:16:25,210 --> 00:16:25,920
Can it be...?

218
00:16:26,410 --> 00:16:30,140
Okama Kenpo:
Memoirs of a Summer's Day!

219
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,770
I see your weakness.

220
00:16:33,510 --> 00:16:34,470
I see through...

221
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:37,100
your Clone-Clone Fruit.

222
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:39,100
Memoirs of a Summer's Day!

223
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:40,400
Joue Shoot!

224
00:16:44,980 --> 00:16:47,360
That's it. No doubt about it.

225
00:16:47,650 --> 00:16:50,860
You see through it, you say?
Through what?!

226
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:55,490
What part of my ability
could someone like you see through?

227
00:16:55,490 --> 00:17:00,330
You can't use your okama kenpo
while in Nami's form, can you?

228
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:06,260
It's true, I might not
be able to attack you.

229
00:17:06,260 --> 00:17:11,340
But the moment you attack me,
you always return to normal...

230
00:17:11,340 --> 00:17:14,560
by touching your cheek
with your left hand.

231
00:17:20,790 --> 00:17:24,600
Huh? What's that?
I can't hear you at all!

232
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:26,190
Hey, I'm right, aren't I?

233
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:30,570
S-So what if you are?!

234
00:17:30,570 --> 00:17:35,280
Yes, yes, without this limber body
that I've developed,

235
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:37,990
through the grueling lessons
of my daily training,

236
00:17:37,990 --> 00:17:41,280
I can't perform my
okama kenpo. So what?

237
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:44,460
You're still plenty
black-and-blue, aren't you?!

238
00:17:44,910 --> 00:17:49,210
What's more, let me show you this—
the prima of okama kenpo!

239
00:17:49,210 --> 00:17:51,170
I'll give you a hint though...

240
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:55,390
From your view, the left is the female,
and the right is the male.

241
00:17:55,390 --> 00:17:56,640
Who cares?!

242
00:17:58,890 --> 00:18:03,140
Whether you see through me or not,
it doesn't matter!

243
00:18:03,140 --> 00:18:04,280
Take this!

244
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:05,440
Okama Kenpo:

245
00:18:06,180 --> 00:18:07,570
Bombardier!

246
00:18:12,150 --> 00:18:14,620
What?! That's the mark
left by his kick?!

247
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:19,570
Good move! Dodging that
was a good move!

248
00:18:19,570 --> 00:18:22,670
At the end of their
bent necks are steel beaks!

249
00:18:23,380 --> 00:18:26,210
There isn't a single crack
around that hole!

250
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:32,170
True power, when focused at a single point,
won't destroy any more than is intended.

251
00:18:32,420 --> 00:18:37,420
Consider one of my kicks
to be like a shot from a rifle.

252
00:18:37,420 --> 00:18:40,770
However, the bullet is a tad
on the large side.

253
00:18:41,090 --> 00:18:43,310
I'm going to perforate you!

254
00:18:43,310 --> 00:18:44,440
Un!

255
00:18:44,930 --> 00:18:45,770
Deux!

256
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:48,150
Collier!

257
00:18:47,330 --> 00:18:48,150
Korrois!

258
00:18:49,570 --> 00:18:51,610
That won't work!

259
00:18:53,530 --> 00:18:56,110
Damn! The difference
in our range doesn't compare!

260
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:01,120
This fight is over, huh?!

261
00:19:01,590 --> 00:19:03,870
Flying, flying, I'm flying!

262
00:19:04,160 --> 00:19:10,300
Okama Kenpo:
Memoirs of a Winter's Sky!

263
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:14,420
But the longer his reach is,
the longer it takes to recover.

264
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:20,260
If I can avoid his shot,
I'll have that much more speed!

265
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:22,640
Time to die!

266
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:30,060
Too bad. How do you like this?

267
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:32,570
Hey, there's something stuck
to your left cheek.

268
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:34,410
Really?

269
00:19:47,850 --> 00:19:48,540
Un!

270
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,010
Deux!

271
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:55,170
Ourrois!

272
00:19:57,360 --> 00:20:00,120
Un! Deux! Ourrois!

273
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:02,350
Un! Deux! Korrois!

274
00:20:02,820 --> 00:20:03,850
Un!

275
00:20:04,390 --> 00:20:05,060
Deux!

276
00:20:05,060 --> 00:20:06,270
Korrois!

277
00:20:11,830 --> 00:20:15,030
Un! Deux! Ourrois!

278
00:20:15,030 --> 00:20:17,920
Un! Deux! Korrois!

279
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:21,160
Un! Deux! Ourrois!

280
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:24,700
Un! Deux! Korrois!

281
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:26,120
Un! Deux!

282
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:27,620
Korrois!

283
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:54,430
Bombardier Arabesque!

284
00:19:35,270 --> 00:19:36,990
Basse Côte!

285
00:19:40,030 --> 00:19:41,540
Longe!

286
00:19:42,290 --> 00:19:43,620
Tendron!

287
00:19:47,290 --> 00:19:48,540
Flanchet!

288
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:55,170
Quasi!

289
00:19:56,680 --> 00:20:00,120
Tendron! Quasi! Collier!
Flanchet! Cuisseau! Jarret!

290
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:03,850
Tendron! Quasi! Collier!
Flanchet! Cuisseau!

291
00:20:03,850 --> 00:20:05,060
Damn it!

292
00:20:05,060 --> 00:20:06,270
Collier!

293
00:20:11,830 --> 00:20:15,850
Jarret! Collier! Quasi!
Flanchet! Gigot! Selle!

294
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:18,780
Queue! Jarret! Collier! Quasi!

295
00:20:18,780 --> 00:20:21,160
Flanchet! Gigot! Selle! Queue!

296
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:27,620
Queue!

297
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:52,360
Veau Shot!

298
00:21:49,120 --> 00:21:51,210
I-I give...

299
00:21:52,080 --> 00:21:55,920
You astound me. You're still alive?

300
00:21:57,290 --> 00:22:00,400
What's the matter? If you turn
yourself into Nami again,

301
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,640
I won't be able to finish you off.

302
00:22:03,380 --> 00:22:06,760
Don't be ridiculous...
With the shape I'm in, I can't move...

303
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:09,430
What good will it do
to avoid the outcome of this?

304
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:13,100
You've won. Kill me.

305
00:22:15,020 --> 00:22:18,930
I'm destined to be eliminated
by the organization anyhow.

306
00:22:19,730 --> 00:22:22,200
What are you waiting for?

307
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:25,070
Hurry up and strike the last blow...

308
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:34,580
That was a good fight.
There's nothing more for us to say.

309
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:48,890
This is, unmistakably, the testament
of friendship between rivals.

310
00:22:48,890 --> 00:22:51,220
But I'm not going to cry...

311
00:22:54,460 --> 00:22:58,410
Bye, now. I'll be taking back
our sharpshooter's goggles.

312
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:01,780
H-He did strike the last blow...

313
00:23:06,330 --> 00:23:09,420
Looks like I've broken
another couple of bones.

314
00:23:23,930 --> 00:23:26,260
E-Everything here is set!

315
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:28,760
We're ready to ignite at any time too!

316
00:23:33,990 --> 00:23:39,980
This palace has basked
in Alabasta's history for 4,000 years.

317
00:23:46,430 --> 00:23:48,430
It has been a source of pride for me.

318
00:23:52,060 --> 00:23:54,660
But if we destroy the royal palace,

319
00:23:54,660 --> 00:23:57,580
the people will stop fighting
and pay attention.

320
00:23:57,580 --> 00:24:02,000
I will be able to tell them the truth
in my own words!

321
00:24:04,580 --> 00:24:06,380
Okay, light them!

322
00:24:06,710 --> 00:24:07,730
Yes!

323
00:24:18,930 --> 00:24:20,440
Wh-What is this?!

324
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:27,110
Are you okay?!

325
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:31,230
It's... him...

326
00:24:33,920 --> 00:24:35,450
We can't have that.

327
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:50,590
That was quite an extreme measure
to take, wasn't it, Miss Wednesday?

328
00:24:51,210 --> 00:24:54,560
This is going to be my house soon.

329
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:56,430
Crocodile!

330
00:24:59,430 --> 00:25:00,790
Your Majesty!

331
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:01,860
Father!

332
00:25:04,410 --> 00:25:07,970
It sure is nice to have a palace, huh?

333
00:25:10,610 --> 00:25:14,450
It's a fine place to look
down on the filth below.

334
00:25:16,700 --> 00:25:17,950
Wh-Where is Luffy?

335
00:25:18,450 --> 00:25:24,420
Huh? You mean Straw Hat?
That puny rookie?

336
00:25:28,090 --> 00:25:29,250
He's...

337
00:25:29,250 --> 00:25:31,090
dead.

